    <abstract><!-- can be changed via merge in the assembly -->
      <para>
        You can install &nm; using <command>zypper</command>. Once you 
        install, you can enable &nm; to start automatically at boot time.</para>
      </abstract>
  </info>
 <para>Install &nm;:</para>
  <screen>&prompt.sudo;zypper install NetworkManager</screen>
 <para>Enable &nm;:</para>
<screen>&prompt.sudo;systemctl enable NetworkManager</screen>
<para>Once &nm; is enabled, the change persists across reboots.</para>
